72static isc_result_t openssldh_todns(const dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *data);
73
74static BIGNUM *bn2 = NULL, *bn768 = NULL, *bn1024 = NULL, *bn1536 = NULL;
75
76#if !HAVE_DH_GET0_KEY
77/*
78 * DH_get0_key, DH_set0_key, DH_get0_pqg and DH_set0_pqg
79 * are from OpenSSL 1.1.0.
80 */
81static void
82DH_get0_key(const DH *dh, const BIGNUM **pub_key, const BIGNUM **priv_key) {
83 if (pub_key != NULL) {
84 *pub_key = dh->pub_key;
85 }
86 if (priv_key != NULL) {
87 *priv_key = dh->priv_key;
88 }
89}
90
91static int
92DH_set0_key(DH *dh, BIGNUM *pub_key, BIGNUM *priv_key) {
93 if (pub_key != NULL) {
94 BN_free(dh->pub_key);
95 dh->pub_key = pub_key;
96 }
97
98 if (priv_key != NULL) {
99 BN_free(dh->priv_key);
100 dh->priv_key = priv_key;
101 }
102
103 return (1);
104}
105
106static void
107DH_get0_pqg(const DH *dh,
108 const BIGNUM **p, const BIGNUM **q, const BIGNUM **g)
109{
110 if (p != NULL) {
111 *p = dh->p;
112 }
113 if (q != NULL) {
114 *q = dh->q;
115 }
116 if (g != NULL) {
117 *g = dh->g;
118 }
119}
120
121static int
122DH_set0_pqg(DH *dh, BIGNUM *p, BIGNUM *q, BIGNUM *g)
123{
124 /* If the fields p and g in d are NULL, the corresponding input
125 * parameters MUST be non-NULL. q may remain NULL.
126 */
127 if ((dh->p == NULL && p == NULL)
128 || (dh->g == NULL && g == NULL))
129 {
130 return 0;
131 }
132
133 if (p != NULL) {
134 BN_free(dh->p);
135 dh->p = p;
136 }
137 if (q != NULL) {
138 BN_free(dh->q);
139 dh->q = q;
140 }
141 if (g != NULL) {
142 BN_free(dh->g);
143 dh->g = g;
144 }
145
146 if (q != NULL) {
147 dh->length = BN_num_bits(q);
148 }
149
150 return (1);
151}
152
153#define DH_clear_flags(d, f) (d)->flags &= ~(f)
154
155#endif /* !HAVE_DH_GET0_KEY */
156
157static isc_result_t
158openssldh_computesecret(const dst_key_t *pub, const dst_key_t *priv,
159 isc_buffer_t *secret)
160{
161 DH *dhpub, *dhpriv;
162 const BIGNUM *pub_key = NULL;
163 int ret;
164 isc_region_t r;
165 unsigned int len;
166
167 REQUIRE(pub->keydata.dh != NULL);
168 REQUIRE(priv->keydata.dh != NULL);
169
170 dhpub = pub->keydata.dh;
171 dhpriv = priv->keydata.dh;
172
173 len = DH_size(dhpriv);
174 isc_buffer_availableregion(secret, &r);
175 if (r.length < len)
176 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
177
178 DH_get0_key(dhpub, &pub_key, NULL);
179 ret = DH_compute_key(r.base, pub_key, dhpriv);
180 if (ret <= 0)
181 return (dst__openssl_toresult2("DH_compute_key",
182 DST_R_COMPUTESECRETFAILURE));
183 isc_buffer_add(secret, len);
184 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
185}
186
187static bool
188openssldh_compare(const dst_key_t *key1, const dst_key_t *key2) {
189 DH *dh1, *dh2;
190 const BIGNUM *pub_key1 = NULL, *pub_key2 = NULL;
191 const BIGNUM *priv_key1 = NULL, *priv_key2 = NULL;
192 const BIGNUM *p1 = NULL, *g1 = NULL, *p2 = NULL, *g2 = NULL;
193
194 dh1 = key1->keydata.dh;
195 dh2 = key2->keydata.dh;
196
197 if (dh1 == NULL && dh2 == NULL)
198 return (true);
199 else if (dh1 == NULL || dh2 == NULL)
200 return (false);
201
202 DH_get0_key(dh1, &pub_key1, &priv_key1);
203 DH_get0_key(dh2, &pub_key2, &priv_key2);
204 DH_get0_pqg(dh1, &p1, NULL, &g1);
205 DH_get0_pqg(dh2, &p2, NULL, &g2);
206
207 if (BN_cmp(p1, p2) != 0 || BN_cmp(g1, g2) != 0 ||
208 BN_cmp(pub_key1, pub_key2) != 0)
209 return (false);
210
211 if (priv_key1 != NULL || priv_key2 != NULL) {
212 if (priv_key1 == NULL || priv_key2 == NULL)
213 return (false);
214 if (BN_cmp(priv_key1, priv_key2) != 0)
215 return (false);
216 }
217 return (true);
218}
219
220static bool
221openssldh_paramcompare(const dst_key_t *key1, const dst_key_t *key2) {
222 DH *dh1, *dh2;
223 const BIGNUM *p1 = NULL, *g1 = NULL, *p2 = NULL, *g2 = NULL;
224
225 dh1 = key1->keydata.dh;
226 dh2 = key2->keydata.dh;
227
228 if (dh1 == NULL && dh2 == NULL)
229 return (true);
230 else if (dh1 == NULL || dh2 == NULL)
231 return (false);
232
233 DH_get0_pqg(dh1, &p1, NULL, &g1);
234 DH_get0_pqg(dh2, &p2, NULL, &g2);
235
236 if (BN_cmp(p1, p2) != 0 || BN_cmp(g1, g2) != 0)
237 return (false);
238 return (true);
239}
240
241static int
242progress_cb(int p, int n, BN_GENCB *cb) {
243 union {
244 void *dptr;
245 void (*fptr)(int);
246 } u;
247
248 UNUSED(n);
249
250 u.dptr = BN_GENCB_get_arg(cb);
251 if (u.fptr != NULL)
252 u.fptr(p);
253 return (1);
254}
255
256static isc_result_t
257openssldh_generate(dst_key_t *key, int generator, void (*callback)(int)) {
258 DH *dh = NULL;
259 BN_GENCB *cb;
260#if OPENSSL_VERSION_NUMBER < 0x10100000L || defined(LIBRESSL_VERSION_NUMBER)
261 BN_GENCB _cb;
262#endif
263 union {
264 void *dptr;
265 void (*fptr)(int);
266 } u;
267
268 if (generator == 0) {
269 if (key->key_size == 768 ||
270 key->key_size == 1024 ||
271 key->key_size == 1536)
272 {
273 BIGNUM *p, *g;
274 dh = DH_new();
275 if (key->key_size == 768)
276 p = BN_dup(bn768);
277 else if (key->key_size == 1024)
278 p = BN_dup(bn1024);
279 else
280 p = BN_dup(bn1536);
281 g = BN_dup(bn2);
282 if (dh == NULL || p == NULL || g == NULL) {
283 if (dh != NULL)
284 DH_free(dh);
285 if (p != NULL)
286 BN_free(p);
287 if (g != NULL)
288 BN_free(g);
289 return (dst__openssl_toresult(ISC_R_NOMEMORY));
290 }
291 DH_set0_pqg(dh, p, NULL, g);
292 } else
293 generator = 2;
294 }
295
296 if (generator != 0) {
297 dh = DH_new();
298 if (dh == NULL)
299 return (dst__openssl_toresult(ISC_R_NOMEMORY));
300 cb = BN_GENCB_new();
301#if OPENSSL_VERSION_NUMBER >= 0x10100000L && !defined(LIBRESSL_VERSION_NUMBER)
302 if (cb == NULL) {
303 DH_free(dh);
304 return (dst__openssl_toresult(ISC_R_NOMEMORY));
305 }
306#endif
307 if (callback == NULL) {
308 BN_GENCB_set_old(cb, NULL, NULL);
309 } else {
310 u.fptr = callback;
311 BN_GENCB_set(cb, &progress_cb, u.dptr);
312 }
313
314 if (!DH_generate_parameters_ex(dh, key->key_size, generator,
315 cb)) {
316 DH_free(dh);
317 BN_GENCB_free(cb);
318 return (dst__openssl_toresult2(
319 "DH_generate_parameters_ex",
320 DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
321 }
322 BN_GENCB_free(cb);
323 cb = NULL;
324 }
325
326 if (DH_generate_key(dh) == 0) {
327 DH_free(dh);
328 return (dst__openssl_toresult2("DH_generate_key",
329 DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
330 }
331 DH_clear_flags(dh, DH_FLAG_CACHE_MONT_P);
332 key->keydata.dh = dh;
333
334 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
335}
336
337static bool
338openssldh_isprivate(const dst_key_t *key) {
339 DH *dh = key->keydata.dh;
340 const BIGNUM *priv_key = NULL;
341
342 DH_get0_key(dh, NULL, &priv_key);
343 return (dh != NULL && priv_key != NULL);
344}
345
346static void
347openssldh_destroy(dst_key_t *key) {
348 DH *dh = key->keydata.dh;
349
350 if (dh == NULL)
351 return;
352
353 DH_free(dh);
354 key->keydata.dh = NULL;
355}
356
357static void
358uint16_toregion(uint16_t val, isc_region_t *region) {
359 *region->base = (val & 0xff00) >> 8;
360 isc_region_consume(region, 1);
361 *region->base = (val & 0x00ff);
362 isc_region_consume(region, 1);
363}
364
365static uint16_t
366uint16_fromregion(isc_region_t *region) {
367 uint16_t val;
368 unsigned char *cp = region->base;
369
370 val = ((unsigned int)(cp[0])) << 8;
371 val |= ((unsigned int)(cp[1]));
372
373 isc_region_consume(region, 2);
374
375 return (val);
376}
377
378static isc_result_t
379openssldh_todns(const dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *data) {
380 DH *dh;
381 const BIGNUM *pub_key = NULL, *p = NULL, *g = NULL;
382 isc_region_t r;
383 uint16_t dnslen, plen, glen, publen;
384
385 REQUIRE(key->keydata.dh != NULL);
386
387 dh = key->keydata.dh;
388
389 isc_buffer_availableregion(data, &r);
390
391 DH_get0_pqg(dh, &p, NULL, &g);
392 if (BN_cmp(g, bn2) == 0 &&
393 (BN_cmp(p, bn768) == 0 ||
394 BN_cmp(p, bn1024) == 0 ||
395 BN_cmp(p, bn1536) == 0)) {
396 plen = 1;
397 glen = 0;
398 }
399 else {
400 plen = BN_num_bytes(p);
401 glen = BN_num_bytes(g);
402 }
403 DH_get0_key(dh, &pub_key, NULL);
404 publen = BN_num_bytes(pub_key);
405 dnslen = plen + glen + publen + 6;
406 if (r.length < (unsigned int) dnslen)
407 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
408
409 uint16_toregion(plen, &r);
410 if (plen == 1) {
411 if (BN_cmp(p, bn768) == 0)
412 *r.base = 1;
413 else if (BN_cmp(p, bn1024) == 0)
414 *r.base = 2;
415 else
416 *r.base = 3;
417 } else
418 BN_bn2bin(p, r.base);
419 isc_region_consume(&r, plen);
420
421 uint16_toregion(glen, &r);
422 if (glen > 0)
423 BN_bn2bin(g, r.base);
424 isc_region_consume(&r, glen);
425
426 uint16_toregion(publen, &r);
427 BN_bn2bin(pub_key, r.base);
428 isc_region_consume(&r, publen);
429
430 isc_buffer_add(data, dnslen);
431
432 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
433}

435static isc_result_t
436openssldh_fromdns(dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *data) {
437 DH *dh;
438 BIGNUM *pub_key = NULL, *p = NULL, *g = NULL;
439 isc_region_t r;
440 uint16_t plen, glen, publen;
441 int special = 0;
442
443 isc_buffer_remainingregion(data, &r);
444 if (r.length == 0)
445 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
446
447 dh = DH_new();
448 if (dh == NULL)
449 return (dst__openssl_toresult(ISC_R_NOMEMORY));
450 DH_clear_flags(dh, DH_FLAG_CACHE_MONT_P);
451
452 /*
453 * Read the prime length. 1 & 2 are table entries, > 16 means a
454 * prime follows, otherwise an error.
455 */
456 if (r.length < 2) {
457 DH_free(dh);
458 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
459 }
460 plen = uint16_fromregion(&r);
461 if (plen < 16 && plen != 1 && plen != 2) {
462 DH_free(dh);
463 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
464 }
465 if (r.length < plen) {
466 DH_free(dh);
467 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
468 }
469 if (plen == 1 || plen == 2) {
470 if (plen == 1) {
471 special = *r.base;
472 isc_region_consume(&r, 1);
473 } else {
474 special = uint16_fromregion(&r);
475 }
476 switch (special) {
477 case 1:
478 p = BN_dup(bn768);
479 break;
480 case 2:
481 p = BN_dup(bn1024);
482 break;
483 case 3:
484 p = BN_dup(bn1536);
485 break;
486 default:
487 DH_free(dh);
488 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
489 }
490 } else {
491 p = BN_bin2bn(r.base, plen, NULL);
492 isc_region_consume(&r, plen);
493 }
494
495 /*
496 * Read the generator length. This should be 0 if the prime was
497 * special, but it might not be. If it's 0 and the prime is not
498 * special, we have a problem.
499 */
500 if (r.length < 2) {
501 DH_free(dh);
502 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
503 }
504 glen = uint16_fromregion(&r);
505 if (r.length < glen) {
506 DH_free(dh);
507 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
508 }
509 if (special != 0) {
510 if (glen == 0)
511 g = BN_dup(bn2);
512 else {
513 g = BN_bin2bn(r.base, glen, NULL);
514 if (g != NULL && BN_cmp(g, bn2) != 0) {
515 DH_free(dh);
516 BN_free(g);
517 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
518 }
519 }
520 } else {
521 if (glen == 0) {
522 DH_free(dh);
523 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
524 }
525 g = BN_bin2bn(r.base, glen, NULL);
526 }
527 isc_region_consume(&r, glen);
528
529 if (p == NULL || g == NULL) {
530 DH_free(dh);
531 if (p != NULL)
532 BN_free(p);
533 if (g != NULL)
534 BN_free(g);
535 return (dst__openssl_toresult(ISC_R_NOMEMORY));
536 }
537 DH_set0_pqg(dh, p, NULL, g);
538
539 if (r.length < 2) {
540 DH_free(dh);
541 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
542 }
543 publen = uint16_fromregion(&r);
544 if (r.length < publen) {
545 DH_free(dh);
546 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
547 }
548 pub_key = BN_bin2bn(r.base, publen, NULL);
549 if (pub_key == NULL) {
550 DH_free(dh);
551 return (dst__openssl_toresult(ISC_R_NOMEMORY));
552 }
553#if (LIBRESSL_VERSION_NUMBER >= 0x2070000fL) && (LIBRESSL_VERSION_NUMBER <= 0x2070200fL)
554 /*
555 * LibreSSL << 2.7.3 DH_get0_key requires priv_key to be set when
556 * DH structure is empty, hence we cannot use DH_get0_key().
557 */
558 dh->pub_key = pub_key;
559#else /* LIBRESSL_VERSION_NUMBER */
560 DH_set0_key(dh, pub_key, NULL);
561#endif /* LIBRESSL_VERSION_NUMBER */
562 isc_region_consume(&r, publen);
563
564 key->key_size = BN_num_bits(p);
565
566 isc_buffer_forward(data, plen + glen + publen + 6);
567
568 key->keydata.dh = dh;
569
570 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
571}

573static isc_result_t
574openssldh_tofile(const dst_key_t *key, const char *directory) {
575 int i;
576 DH *dh;
577 const BIGNUM *pub_key = NULL, *priv_key = NULL, *p = NULL, *g = NULL;
578 dst_private_t priv;
579 unsigned char *bufs[4];
580 isc_result_t result;
581
582 if (key->keydata.dh == NULL)
583 return (DST_R_NULLKEY);
584
585 if (key->external)
586 return (DST_R_EXTERNALKEY);
587
588 dh = key->keydata.dh;
589 DH_get0_key(dh, &pub_key, &priv_key);
590 DH_get0_pqg(dh, &p, NULL, &g);
591
592 memset(bufs, 0, sizeof(bufs));
593 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
594 bufs[i] = isc_mem_get(key->mctx, BN_num_bytes(p));
595 if (bufs[i] == NULL) {
596 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
597 goto fail;
598 }
599 }
600
601 i = 0;
602
603 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_DH_PRIME;
604 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(p);
605 BN_bn2bin(p, bufs[i]);
606 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
607 i++;
608
609 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_DH_GENERATOR;
610 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(g);
611 BN_bn2bin(g, bufs[i]);
612 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
613 i++;
614
615 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_DH_PRIVATE;
616 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(priv_key);
617 BN_bn2bin(priv_key, bufs[i]);
618 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
619 i++;
620
621 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_DH_PUBLIC;
622 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(pub_key);
623 BN_bn2bin(pub_key, bufs[i]);
624 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
625 i++;
626
627 priv.nelements = i;
628 result = dst__privstruct_writefile(key, &priv, directory);
629 fail:
630 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
631 if (bufs[i] == NULL)
632 break;
633 isc_mem_put(key->mctx, bufs[i], BN_num_bytes(p));
634 }
635 return (result);
636}

638static isc_result_t
639openssldh_parse(dst_key_t *key, isc_lex_t *lexer, dst_key_t *pub) {
640 dst_private_t priv;
641 isc_result_t ret;
642 int i;
643 DH *dh = NULL;
644 BIGNUM *pub_key = NULL, *priv_key = NULL, *p = NULL, *g = NULL;
645 isc_mem_t *mctx;
646#define DST_RET(a) {ret = a; goto err;}
647
648 UNUSED(pub);
649 mctx = key->mctx;
650
651 /* read private key file */
652 ret = dst__privstruct_parse(key, DST_ALG_DH, lexer, mctx, &priv);
653 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
654 return (ret);
655
656 if (key->external)
657 DST_RET(DST_R_EXTERNALKEY);
658
659 dh = DH_new();
660 if (dh == NULL)
661 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
662 DH_clear_flags(dh, DH_FLAG_CACHE_MONT_P);
663 key->keydata.dh = dh;
664
665 for (i = 0; i < priv.nelements; i++) {
666 BIGNUM *bn;
667 bn = BN_bin2bn(priv.elements[i].data,
668 priv.elements[i].length, NULL);
669 if (bn == NULL)
670 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
671
672 switch (priv.elements[i].tag) {
673 case TAG_DH_PRIME:
674 p = bn;
675 break;
676 case TAG_DH_GENERATOR:
677 g = bn;
678 break;
679 case TAG_DH_PRIVATE:
680 priv_key = bn;
681 break;
682 case TAG_DH_PUBLIC:
683 pub_key = bn;
684 break;
685 }
686 }
687 dst__privstruct_free(&priv, mctx);
688 DH_set0_key(dh, pub_key, priv_key);
689 DH_set0_pqg(dh, p, NULL, g);
690
691 key->key_size = BN_num_bits(p);
692 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
693
694 err:
695 if (p != NULL)
696 BN_free(p);
697 if (g != NULL)
698 BN_free(g);
699 if (pub_key != NULL)
700 BN_free(pub_key);
701 if (priv_key != NULL)
702 BN_free(priv_key);
703 openssldh_destroy(key);
704 dst__privstruct_free(&priv, mctx);
705 isc_safe_memwipe(&priv, sizeof(priv));
706 return (ret);
707}
708
709static void
710openssldh_cleanup(void) {
711 BN_free(bn2);
712 bn2 = NULL;
713
714 BN_free(bn768);
715 bn768 = NULL;
716
717 BN_free(bn1024);
718 bn1024 = NULL;
719
720 BN_free(bn1536);
721 bn1536 = NULL;
722}
723
724static dst_func_t openssldh_functions = {
725 NULL, /*%< createctx */
726 NULL, /*%< createctx2 */
727 NULL, /*%< destroyctx */
728 NULL, /*%< adddata */
729 NULL, /*%< openssldh_sign */
730 NULL, /*%< openssldh_verify */
731 NULL, /*%< openssldh_verify2 */
732 openssldh_computesecret,
733 openssldh_compare,
734 openssldh_paramcompare,
735 openssldh_generate,
736 openssldh_isprivate,
737 openssldh_destroy,
738 openssldh_todns,
739 openssldh_fromdns,
740 openssldh_tofile,
741 openssldh_parse,
742 openssldh_cleanup,
743 NULL, /*%< fromlabel */
744 NULL, /*%< dump */
745 NULL, /*%< restore */
746};
747
748isc_result_t
749dst__openssldh_init(dst_func_t **funcp) {
750 REQUIRE(funcp != NULL);
751 if (*funcp == NULL) {
752 if (BN_hex2bn(&bn2, PRIME2) == 0 || bn2 == NULL) {
753 goto cleanup;
754 }
755 if (BN_hex2bn(&bn768, PRIME768) == 0 || bn768 == NULL) {
756 goto cleanup;
757 }
758 if (BN_hex2bn(&bn1024, PRIME1024) == 0 || bn1024 == NULL) {
759 goto cleanup;
760 }
761 if (BN_hex2bn(&bn1536, PRIME1536) == 0 || bn1536 == NULL) {
762 goto cleanup;
763 }
764 *funcp = &openssldh_functions;
765 }
766 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
767
768 cleanup:
769 if (bn2 != NULL) BN_free(bn2);
770 if (bn768 != NULL) BN_free(bn768);
771 if (bn1024 != NULL) BN_free(bn1024);
772 if (bn1536 != NULL) BN_free(bn1536);
773 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
774}
